\n<Rui>Somehow, we've gotten used to living here, haven't we? At
first, I was definitely a bit anxious.
1ワンズ普通

\n<Ones>Rui, it's been quite a while since we came here. At first, I
thought it was a rather unpleasant town, but you get used to
it if you live long enough.

\n<Rui>I was worried someone from home might come and find us, but
it seems we're safe! That's a relief♥

\n<Rui>I thought maybe pursuers from home would come after us, but
it looks like we're okay.
\n<Rui>Geez! Grandpa!?
\n<Old Man>Phew... I've finally found you. Young master. Young lady.
1ルイ困惑
\n<Rui>...that's the situation. Grandpa, do you understand?
1ワンズ困惑
\n<Ones>...that's how it is. I'm sorry, Grandpa. Do you understand?

\n<Old Man>Hmm. Well, it's mostly as I expected. I understand the
feelings of both the young master and the young lady. I have
no intention of taking you back immediately. Please be at
ease.

\n<Old Man>Let's have a little talk about the history of the Catfield
family. And the real reason why Miss Chelsea was expelled
from the house.

\n<Old Man>In the old days, "humans" and "beastmen" were clearly
distinguished. It was a time when humans treated beastmen as
slaves. You know this from your lessons.

\n<Old Man>Compared to humans, beastmen often have superior physical
abilities. Yet, why were they treated as slaves... The
reason is simple. Humans were numerous and united.

\n<Old Man>On the other hand, beastmen have various roots in their
ancestry. Cats, dogs, raccoons, rabbits, foxes, and so on...
It's natural that they weren't united.

\n<Old Man>The majority of humans discriminated against beastmen,
scorned them, and made them serve. There was such an era.
But now, that is no longer the case.

\n<Old Man>The first head of the Catfield family united the scattered
beastmen and stood up for the rights of beastmen together.
Regardless of being cats or dogs, they rose up to demand
their rights.

\n<Old Man>After many years, humans and beastmen reconciled. They are
equal and good friends.

\n<Old Man>Now beastmen are treated as humans too. You two may not feel
it much since you were born in an era where this is normal.

\n<Old Man>However, this is where the problem starts. After the
discrimination against beastmen disappeared. Now, let me
tell you about what is happening at present.

\n<Old Man>What happens when discrimination disappears? When a negative
becomes zero, it doesn't end there. With that momentum, it
moves from zero to positive.

\C[14]\n<Old Man>"Beastmen are special."\C[0] That's the idea. They should be
favored now for all the oppression they've suffered before.
That's how the ideology shifted.

\n<Old Man>The current head of the family... your father has become
what is called "beastmen supremacy." The belief that
beastmen are superior to humans.

\n<Old Man>Miss Chelsea has always been fair to everyone. Whether human
or beastman, she treated everyone equally and fought with
them fairly. She fought equally and made up equally.

\n<Old Man>And before you knew it, there were many smiles around Miss
Chelsea. She had a mysterious charm that way. She didn't
care whether someone was human or beastman at all.

\n<Old Man>The head of the family could not tolerate this. "Being equal
to humans," that was considered "the shame of the Catfield
family."
1ルイ困惑
\n<Rui>Why did you tell us this now, Grandpa?
1ワンズ困惑
\n<Ones>Why are you telling us this now, Grandpa?

\n<Old Man>I have served the Catfield family for generations. However,
I do not believe that the current head's views are correct.

\n<Old Man>If you two lived surrounded by beastmen in that house
without any inconvenience, surely you would come to share
the same ideology as the head of the family.

\n<Old Man>This is also a good opportunity. I thought it might be good
for you to continue your social studies for a while longer.
In exchange, I will also stay here.

\n<Old Man>Anyway, don't do anything reckless. If I judge something to

Understood?
